title: Ugandan university drops mandatory pregnancy tests for students after outcry
description: A university in Uganda has withdrawn a requirement for female nursing and midwifery students to take a pregnancy test before sitting their exams, after facing a backlash.

title: Iranian archer joins other athletes in showing support for protests
description: Iranian archer Parmida Ghasemi demonstrated her support for anti-government protests by removing her hijab during an awards ceremony in Tehran, a video shared to social media on Thursday shows.

title: China's Singles Day sales could top 1 trillion yuan even as the economy cools
description: China's Singles Day, the world's biggest annual shopping event, is known for regularly smashing sales records.

title: The UK economy is sliding into recession and Europe is set to follow
description: The UK economy shrank in the third quarter, signaling the start of a recession that is likely to hit Europe next.

title: Hong Kong jails woman for insulting China's national anthem during Olympic celebration
description: A woman who waved a British colonial-era flag to celebrate Hong Kong claiming Olympic gold has become the first person in the city to be jailed on a charge of insulting the Chinese national anthem.

title: Australia blames Russian-linked ransomware gang for Medibank data breach
description: Cyber criminals with links to Russia are behind a ransomware attack on one of Australia's largest private health insurers that's seen sensitive personal data published to the dark web, the Australian Federal Police (AFP) said Friday.

title: Analysis: Elon Musk's Twitter faces its 'Titanic' moment as executives and advertisers flee while trolls run rampant
description: The world is watching the world's richest man single-handedly destroy one of the world's most powerful and important communication platforms, just weeks after acquiring it for $44 billion. And of course, the world is watching the dramatic spectacle unfold on — where else? — Twitter.

title: Indonesian plane's faulty throttle reported 65 times before fatal crash: investigators
description: A faulty automatic engine throttle system that was not properly monitored by pilots led to a deadly January 2021 crash of a Sriwijaya 737-500 jet, Indonesia's air accident investigator KNKT said in a final report on Thursday.

title: France suspends deal to take in thousands of asylum-seekers currently in Italy after row over ship
description: The diplomatic fallout between France and Italy over a stranded migrant ship in the Mediterranean Sea is far from over.
